S' A RESOURCE INFORMATION SYSTEM FOR WILDLAND MANAGEMENT.WRIS (WILDLAND RESOURCE INFORMATION SYSTEM) IS A COMPUTER SYSTEM FORPROCESSING, STORING, RETRIEVING, UPDATING, AND DISPLAYING GEOGRAPHIC DATA. THEPOLYGON, REPRESENTING A LAND AREA BOUNDARY, FORMS THE BUILDING BLOCK OF WRIS.POLYGONS FORM A MAP. MAPS ARE DIGITISED MANUALLY OR BY AUTOMATIC SCANNING.COMPUTER PROGRAMMES CAN EXTRACT AND PRODUCE POLYGON MAPS AND CAN OVERLAY,PLOT, AND STORE THEM, AS WELL AS AGGREGATE ACREAGES AND PRINT SUMMARIES. WRISIS FUNCTIONALLY ORIENTED TOWARD TIMBER MANAGEMENT, BUT CAN BE USED FOR OTHERTYPES OF RESOURCE ACTIVITIES